 prime at forty-nine. Anna herself lived to ninety-three, dying May 10, 1992 in Boxford, Massachusetts."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Both sons born in France","body":"Anna married Winthrop Perrin Haynes — who had served as a 2nd Lieutenant in World War I — in Boxford on August 10, 1925. Both their sons, Lewis Rogerson (1926) and Edward Hamilton (1928), were born in Neuilly-sur-Seine, France, where the family was then living."},{"number":3,"category":"legacy","header":"Her father's playground is still a Boxford landmark","body":"The Lewis Kennedy Morse Playground, donated posthumously by her stepmother Ednah Rich Morse and dedicated October 31, 1930, commemorated Anna's father on the grounds of what is now Cole School in Boxford. The Haynes family estate on Main Street — the Pearson-Morse-Haynes house — was named Elmlea and became the Elmlea Tree Farm."}],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Hooker","description":"Named Anna Hooker — honoring the Hooker lineage through her mother Annie Hooker Capron."}],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM556"},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"sources":[{"short":"FindAGrave + FamilySearch"}],"research_sources":[],"slug":"anna-morse-1899"},"I01204":{"id":"I01204","is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"former_ids":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Lewis Kennedy Morse","first_name":"Lewis","middle_name":"Kennedy","last_name":"Morse","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1779507241/lewismorse_bzyti4.png","photo_notes":"Portrait. Cloudinary."},"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1869,"month":7,"day":23,"city":"Boston","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1930,"month":3,"day":8,"city":"Manhattan","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,